H0.text: Where in the body is the zygomatic major muscle. Cheek

H1.text: Where in the body is the zygomatic major muscle. Temple

H2.text: Where in the body is the zygomatic major muscle. Jawline

H3.text: Where in the body is the zygomatic major muscle. Jowl

A4.text: It arises from the zygomatic arch (cheekbone).

A5.text: It originates from the superior margin of the lateral surface of the temporal process of zygomatic bone.

A6.text: below this foramen is a slight elevation, which gives origin to the zygomaticus muscle.
